{
  "text": "[17] The relationship of discharge to permeability was investigated using the high-permeability results of [CITATION_1] as a starting point. She modeled a 10 À11 m 2 hydrothermal system which included the magma chamber implicitly through a heat flux boundary condition based on the analytical solution to the conductive heat flow through the wall of an infinitely long cylinder. This implies that no heat was lost through the roof and floor of the . The total discharge of the k = 10 À16 m 2 model, in kilograms, appears above its curve. The numbers above the other curves denote the fraction of this discharge that their corresponding models produced.",
